OL,3,CCouncil tax up and energy bills down:
OL,4,CHousehold bill changes coming in April
OL,6,FThe regulator, Ofgem, has announced it
OL,7,Fis dropping its price cap by 12.3%. In
OL,8,Freal terms that means a typical dual-
OL,9,Ffuel household in England, Scotland
OL,10,Fand Wales should see a drop of #238
OL,11,Fover the course of a year or around
OL,12,F#20 a month.
OL,14,FBut energy is not the only household
OL,15,Fbill which is expected to change come
OL,16,FApril 1 - council tax and tax free
OL,17,Fchildcare are also expected to be
OL,18,Fdifferent in the new financial year.
